ZhH48EfH,PUBG-EquilizerAPO-CFG.txt,Sticky2000,INI file,Tuesday 16th of April 2024 06:30:09 PM CDT,"# This is a basic configuration for Equalizer APO to enhance the sound of footsteps in PUBG based on the provided spectrogram.
# It boosts mid-range frequencies where the detail of footsteps is present, and slightly attenuates very low and very high frequencies.
# Low frequencies: Slight reduction to decrease rumble and focus more on footsteps.
Filter: ON PK Fc 150 Hz Gain -2 dB Q 1.4
# Lower mid frequencies: Some reduction to clear up the muddiness.
Filter: ON PK Fc 300 Hz Gain -1.5 dB Q 1.4
# Mid frequencies: Boosting to emphasize the sound of footsteps.
Filter: ON PK Fc 1000 Hz Gain 3 dB Q 1.2
Filter: ON PK Fc 1500 Hz Gain 2 dB Q 1.2
# Upper mid frequencies: These are important for the detail of footsteps.
Filter: ON PK Fc 2000 Hz Gain 4 dB Q 1.2
Filter: ON PK Fc 2500 Hz Gain 3 dB Q 1.2
# High frequencies: A slight boost for the crispness of footsteps but careful not to make it too harsh.
Filter: ON PK Fc 3500 Hz Gain 2 dB Q 1.4
Filter: ON PK Fc 4000 Hz Gain 1.5 dB Q 1.4
# Very high frequencies: Taming these a bit as they can contribute to noise.
Filter: ON PK Fc 6000 Hz Gain -2 dB Q 1.4
Filter: ON PK Fc 7000 Hz Gain -2.5 dB Q 1.4
# Apply a high shelf filter if the very high frequencies are too pronounced.
Filter: ON HS Fc 8000 Hz Gain -3 dB Q 1.0"
